%N A173571 Decimal expansion of constant related to Goat Problem, Donkey Problem, Tenenbaum and A173201.
%H A173571 Marshall Fraser, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2690163">A tale of two goats</a>, Math. Mag., 55 (1982), 221-227. Has extensive bibliography. [From _N. J. A. Sloane_, Jul 12 2011]
%H A173571 Gerd Lamprecht, <a href="http://www.gerdlamprecht.de/Roemisch_JAVA.htm#ZZZZZ0003">Iterationsrechner Beispiel 3</a>.
%F A173571 Equals sqrt(1 - A072112^2) = sqrt(1 - (1-A133731^2/2)^2), with A072112 = 1 - A133731^2/2 and A133731 = 2*cos(A173201/2).
%F A173571 A075838 = (x + Pi/2 - arcsin(x))/A133731^2, where x is this constant.
%e A173571 0.94444337820557904649220860421297849982111601877163...
%t A173571 RealDigits[Chop[x /. FindRoot[Pi*Sqrt[1 - x^2] + x - Sqrt[1 - x^2]*ArcCos[Sqrt[1 - x^2]] == Pi/2, {x, 1}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]]][[1]] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Apr 22 2026 *)
%Y A173571 Cf. A072112, A075838, A133731, A173201.
